\cf0 \strokec2 Why do we not use acryl?\
Acrylic nail extensions were once very popular, but today they are less common because newer, safer, and more natural-looking methods (like gel or acrygel) have taken their place. Acrylic has a strong chemical smell, can be harsh on the natural nail, and is less flexible, which makes it more prone to lifting or breaking. Modern gels and hybrid systems are lighter, more durable, look more natural, and are healthier for the nails. They also allow for easier application and removal, giving a more comfortable experience for both clients and stylists.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
